  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to assess if curcumin, a commonly used food spice, can regress
      colorectal adenomatous polyps in patients with familial adenomatous polyposis, an inherited
      form of colorectal cancer.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <overall_status>Withdrawn</overall_status>
  <why_stopped>
    Subsequent data generated by our collaborators have shown efficacy with curcumin and quercetin
    in 5 patients in a non placebo controlled trial.
  </why_stopped>
